pageContext.claim: “… the World Health Organization which we've now officially pulled out of.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump's decision to withdraw the United States from the World Health Organization was not formalized until more than a month later, in a letter dated July 6. Officials said in response that they were reviewing whether the United States had met the conditions for withdrawal, including paying outstanding membership dues of $198 million. The withdrawal would not take effect until July 2021.
